Sorry I spaced that you had both pc and Xbox lol. Same idea;

Pc gets 2+ ethernets ran to it, one for video unless you're doing dual monitors or something, and one for dual USB 2.0. Might be able to do a single USB 3.0 too, never tried. Some combo wireless keyboard mouse combos share a receiver if you don't want to run multiple ethernets for more USBs, or you can try a USB hub to split the signal to multiple USB devices instead of running multiple ethernets. I would use a powered hub.

Tvs have input generally so just swap from HDMI 1 or 2 to go between pc and Xbox.

